Q1. Python Data Types
TypeDescriptionExampleintWhole numbers, no decimalage = 20floatNumbers with decimal pointprice = 99.5strText enclosed in quotesname = "Gargi"boolOnly True or Falseis_student = True
pythonx = 10          # int
y = 3.14        # float
z = "Hello"     # str
flag = True     # bool

print(type(x))  # <class 'int'>
print(type(y))  # <class 'float'>
print(type(z))  # <class 'str'>
print(type(flag)) # <class 'bool'>
Key difference: int stores exact whole numbers, float stores decimals, str stores text, and bool stores only two logical values.

